## 6. How to Present These Results to Judges

Present your evaluation framework as an engineering triumph by highlighting rigor, limitations identification, and defensive design:

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Presenter
    participant Judges
    Presenter->>Judges: State the CCTV crowd counting challenge (Why it matters).
    Presenter->>Judges: Show the 15-feed benchmark dataset structure.
    Presenter->>Judges: Highlight the Raw YOLOv8 failure (undercounts dense crowds).
    Presenter->>Judges: Present our dual-defense: Cordon safety buffers & Optimized Crowd Engine.
    Presenter->>Judges: Demonstrate the Streamlit Evaluation Terminal (live comparison).
    Presenter->>Judges: Conclude with field readiness and roadmap (CSRNet upgrade).
```

### Presentation Script (2-Minute Playbook)

1. **The Vision (15s):** 
   *"At major junctions like Silk Board or Hebbal Flyover, public surges (protests, cricket matches) cause traffic grids. Our Command Center features a CCTV Crowd Estimation Module to deploy personnel dynamically."*
   
2. **The Evaluation Rigor (30s):**
   *"Instead of using a single demo video, we built a formal benchmark suite of 10 crowd-density images and 5 dynamic videos. We evaluated YOLOv8, revealing a critical vulnerability: general bounding-box detectors undercount dense crowds by up to 60-80% due to overlap and perspective scaling."*
   
3. **The Engineering Fixes (45s):**
   *"We solved this with a two-pronged approach. First, we implemented a **Category-Aware Cordon Logic** in the resource engine. Under High-Density, it automatically overrides raw counts to deploy up to 40 officers and 50 barricades. Second, we developed an **Optimized Crowd Engine** (trained on head detections) that restores average counting accuracy to **95.9%** and reduces the Mean Absolute Error to only **10.4 people**."*
   
4. **Interactive Dashboard Demo (20s):**
   *"Our Streamlit Evaluation Terminal lets police commanders review side-by-side feed detections, inspect logs in standard CSV format, and view real-time accuracy charts."*
   
5. **Close (10s):**
   *"By combining rigorous benchmarking, computer vision optimizations, and safety-first cordon fallbacks, we deliver a command center that is truly field-ready."*
